The 14-year-old daughter of the late conservationist Steve Irwin is returning to television to be the face of Hallmark's new Friday night family movie showcase. The Australian crocodile hunter's child will star in "Return to Nim's Island," the sequel of the 2008 flick "Nim's Island." It will be her first feature-length film, but far from her first time on television.
